label.value: lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C, C-O, C-N and other bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond. They differ from other enzymes in that two substrates are involved in one reaction direction, but only one in the other direction. When acting on the single substrate, a molecule is eliminated and this generates either a new double bond or a new ring.

label.value: carbon-carbon lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond.

label.value: carboxy-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the nonhydrolytic addition or removal of a carboxyl group to or from a compound.

label.value: aldehyde-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond in a molecule containing a hydroxyl group and a carbonyl group to form two smaller molecules, each being an aldehyde or a ketone.

label.value: oxo-acid-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, of a 3-hydroxy acid.

label.value: carbon-oxygen lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the breakage of a carbon-oxygen bond.

label.value: hydro-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond by elimination of water.

label.value: carbon-oxygen lyase activity, acting on polysaccharides

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond by the elimination of an alcohol from a polysaccharide.

label.value: carbon-oxygen lyase activity, acting on phosphates

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond by elimination of a phosphate.

label.value: carbon-nitrogen lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the release of ammonia or one of its derivatives, with the formation of a double bond or ring. Enzymes with this activity may catalyze the actual elimination of the ammonia, amine or amide, e.g. CH-CH(-NH-R) -eq- C-eq-CH- + NH2-R. Others, however, catalyze elimination of another component, e.g. water, which is followed by spontaneous reactions that lead to breakage of the C-N bond, e.g. L-serine ammonia-lyase (EC - 4.3.1.17), so that the overall reaction is C(-OH)-CH(-NH2) -eq- CH2-CO- + NH3, i.e. an elimination with rearrangement. The sub-subclasses of EC - 4.3 are the ammonia-lyases (EC - 4.3.1), lyases acting on amides, amidines, etc. (EC - 4.3.2), the amine-lyases (EC - 4.3.3), and other carbon-nitrogen lyases (EC - 4.3.99).

label.value: ammonia-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the release of ammonia by the cleavage of a carbon-nitrogen bond or the reverse reaction with ammonia as a substrate.

label.value: amidine-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the release of amides or amidines by the cleavage of a carbon-nitrogen bond or the reverse reaction with an amide or amidine as a substrate.

label.value: amine-lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the release of amides by the cleavage of a carbon-nitrogen bond or the reverse reaction with an amine as a substrate.

label.value: strictosidine synthase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  3alpha(S)-strictosidine + H(2)O -eq- secologanin + tryptamine.

label.value: carbon-sulfur lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the elimination of hydrogen sulfide or substituted H2S.

label.value: carbon-halide lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the breakage of a bond between carbon and any halogen atom.

label.value: phosphorus-oxygen lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a phosphorus-oxygen bond by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond.

label.value: magnesium chelatase activity

label.value: cis-trans isomerase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of a reaction that interconverts cis and trans isomers. Atoms or groups are termed cis or trans to one another when they lie respectively on the same or on opposite sides of a reference plane identifiable as common among stereoisomers.

label.value: intramolecular oxidoreductase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which the hydrogen donor and acceptor are the same molecule, and no oxidized product appears.

label.value: intramolecular oxidoreductase activity, interconverting aldoses and ketoses

label.value: intramolecular transferase activity, phosphotransferases
